.TH "fsl_esai_set_dai_sysclk" 9 "fsl_esai_set_dai_sysclk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_esai_set_dai_sysclk \- configure the clock frequency of MCLK (HCKT/HCKR)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_esai_set_dai_sysclk
.BI "(struct snd_soc_dai *dai "  ","
.BI "int clk_id "  ","
.BI "unsigned int freq "  ","
.BI "int dir "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dai" 12
pointer to DAI
.IP "clk_id" 12
The clock source of HCKT/HCKR
(Input from outside; output from inside, FSYS or EXTAL)
.IP "freq" 12
The required clock rate of HCKT/HCKR
.IP "dir" 12
The clock direction of HCKT/HCKR
.SH "NOTE"
If the direction is input, we do not care about clk_id.
